    "discriminators": [
     "A struck bell: a hard transient followed by a LONG, strongly pitched, inharmonic metallic ring. A long decay_time_seconds_60db with high harmonicity AND high inharmonicity together is the bell fingerprint - a clock tick has neither.",
     "Westminster sequences and hour strikes are widely spaced, so onset_rate stays well under one per second.",
     "Against BELLS-LARGE, BELLS-HANDBELL and METAL-TONAL: exactly the same physics. Only text ('clock', 'grandfather', 'toll', 'strike') puts it here.",
     "Alarm clocks are ALARMS-CLOCK, by UCS decree, not this."
    ],
