    "discriminators": [
     "The textbook rhythmic case and the most confidently separable entry in this batch: SPARSE, PERFECTLY PERIODIC, dry impulses. onset_periodicity sits near 1.0 at an onset_rate of about 1-2 per second (a 1 Hz seconds hand, a 2 Hz tick-tock, a 4-6 Hz watch balance at the fast end), with near-silence between events and a very high crest factor.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-RATCHET: identical impulse, an order of magnitude faster and driven by a single hand motion. onset_rate_per_second alone separates them.",
     "Against MECHANICAL-CLICK: one click, not a train. Against dense textures such as RAIN: rain is STOCHASTIC and onset_periodicity collapses. This is the feature the whole spec was built around.",
     "Against CLOCKS-MECHANICS: a bare tick is just the escapement; MECHANICS is the whole gear train, winding and pendulum, which is far denser and less periodic."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "MECHRtch",
     "MECHClik",
     "CLOCKMech",
     "ALRMClok",
     "MECHRelay"
    ],
